OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FArchie Battersbee's family 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fcan appeal life-support    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fruling                     
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The parents of a 12-year-old boy in a  
OL,6, coma have been given the right to      
OL,7, appeal against the decision to allow   
OL,8, his life-support treatment to end.     
OL,10,FLast week, a High Court judge ruled    
OL,11,Fthat Archie Battersbee was "brain-stem 
OL,12,Fdead" and treatment could stop.        
OL,14,FHowever, following another hearing, the
OL,15,Fsame judge, Mrs Justice Arbuthnot,     
OL,16,Fgranted Archie's parents permission to 
OL,17,Ftake the case to the Court of Appeal.  
OL,19,FArchie's family were "delighted" at the
OL,20,Fdecision, a spokeswoman said.          
